            "summary": "Microsoft Corporation co-founder and billionaire philanthropist, Bill Gates, recently criticized Tesla CEO Elon Musk for actions he believes are harming the world's poorest children. Gates expressed concerns in an interview with the Financial Times regarding Musk's decision to significantly reduce funding for the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID) in February. The cuts have led to the expiration of life-saving food and medicines in warehouses, potentially causing a resurgence of diseases like measles, HIV, and polio. Gates, once the world's richest man, highlighted the impact of these abrupt cuts on vulnerable populations. Musk and the White House did not immediately respond to Benzinga's request for comment. Gates remarked, \"The picture of the world's richest man killing the world's poorest children is not a pretty one.\" This criticism raises questions about the implications of reducing aid to critical global health programs.",
